description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a qualified Care Navigator (Afc B4) to join the core team of the Barrow Integrated Care Community (ICC) The Care Navigator will work flexibly for 30 hours per week based within Fairfield Lane Barrow with travel across the Barrow/Millom ICC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a self-motivated, friendly and proactive person who is passionate about improving health and well-being&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barrow ICC was created to help bring together local health and care organisations, voluntary and 3rd sector teams to ensure that local people are supported to improve their own health and well-being, and that when people are ill or need support, they receive the best possible joined up care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a requirement for the post holder to have the Assistant Practitioner role along with excellent written and verbal communication skills with computer literacy, and good organisational and time management skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work proactively with our community to build future care plans, undertake basic observations, attend external health festivals and offer signposting/navigation to prevent social isolation and making best use of our community assets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anyone newly appointed to the trust will be subject to the completion of a satisfactory 6 month probationary period (this includes bank staff). This will give the new staff member an opportunity to become familiar with the role and working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This vacancy may close earlier than advertised if high numbers of applications are received.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMaxine BaronJob titleICC Development LeadAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Maxine Baron with any questions you may have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;maxine.baron@mbht.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
